    <Folder>
      <name>Disc 1: United States</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Tail o' the Pup]]></name>
        <description>Tony ate chili dogs, but craved a hot dog without chili</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1810-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -118.3797688,34.077357,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Pink's Hot Dogs]]></name>
        <description>Many hot dog variations. Tony liked the millennium hot dog even though he was skeptical at first.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1810-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -118.3442797,34.0838505,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Oki Dog</name>
        <description><![CDATA[He called the pastrami burrito dog "strange" and said it shattered his newly found appreciation of California]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1810-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -118.3612639,34.0870913,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Campanile</name>
        <description>Tony did a guest chef spot at this French restaurant. Tony did a guest chef spot at this French restaurant. Classic bistro style food.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -118.3437462,34.0825122,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Santa Monica Farmers Market</name>
        <description>Fresh produce</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1578-673AB7</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -118.4981603,34.0166132,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Kindle's Donuts]]></name>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B-nodesc</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -118.3004751,33.9452496,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Fred 62</name>
        <description>Tony ate a burger</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1530-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -118.2915368,34.104636,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>The French Laundry</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony was extremely excited to eat at this restaurant, called Thomas Keller "the top of his game" and best chef at that time. Tony eats with Michael Ruhlman, Eric Ripert, and Scott Bryan (who owned Veritas, which was one of Tony's favorite NY restaurants)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.3649712,38.4044403,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Swan Oyster Depot</name>
        <description>Oysters, crabs</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.4209653,37.7909711,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Polly Ann Ice Cream</name>
        <description>Ice cream. Lots of Asian flavors</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1607-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.4977105,37.7534713,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Barney Greengrass</name>
        <description>Breakfast. Tony ate the smoked sturgeon platter.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -73.9745726,40.7879674,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>The Milling Room</name>
        <description><![CDATA[On the show he visited Veritas, which is now closed (Scott Bryan's restaurant). This is Scott's new restaurant. Tony said Veritas was one of his favorite NY restaurants]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -73.974468,40.783747,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Murray's Cheese Bar]]></name>
        <description>Tony did a cheese tasting</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1578-673AB7</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -74.003164,40.731215,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Papaya King</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony's favorite hot dog. He hated the Upper East Side then; he ended up moving there. He still loved the hot dogs.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1810-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -73.9540821,40.7790673,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Brasserie Les Halles</name>
        <description>Restaurant Tony worked at before and during the filming of the show. Permanently closed now.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-BDBDBD</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -73.9836056,40.7435588,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Lobster Pot Restaurant</name>
